<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Paladin to marry a Nec?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?SunOfEris">SunOfEris</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:24 p.m. 7/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Paladin to marry a Nec?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/the_rathe.cgi?read=108" TARGET=_self>Paladin to marry a Nec?</A> (GluG)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> this was announced on the Rallos Zek server.

<BR>&gt; A server that alot of people act like is a
<BR>&gt; True RP server due to the PvP status.
<P>&gt; Lets look at theis closer.
<P>&gt; A Paladin in EQ
<P>&gt; - Paladins are the very picture of a holy
<BR>&gt; knight, fighting for the cause of good in
<BR>&gt; all aspects of his life. They share some of
<BR>&gt; the power of a Cleric, and
<P>&gt; a good deal of the fighting ability of a
<BR>&gt; Warrior, but have a few powers all their
<BR>&gt; own.
<P>&gt; Wishes to Wed a Necromancer
<P>&gt; -These are the dark brotherhood of the
<BR>&gt; arcane arts, dabbling in death. Through evil
<BR>&gt; spiritually based spells, they are able to
<BR>&gt; animate dead bodies
<P>&gt; and skeletons to do their bidding, as well
<BR>&gt; as having spells which leach life from their
<BR>&gt; victims.
<P>&gt; This is EQs own definition of the Classes.
<BR>&gt; Not TSR's, not some Book authers, not some
<BR>&gt; history novel and not some Players. Not even
<BR>&gt; mine.
<P>&gt; Now my beef with this is that Paladins and
<BR>&gt; other players who claim to be Roleplaying
<BR>&gt; are not seeing a Problem with this. Whole
<BR>&gt; guilds of Paladins
<P>&gt; are for it. I just wish they all would be
<BR>&gt; abondoned by their chosen EQ God for
<BR>&gt; embracing Evil, striped of their powers and
<BR>&gt; forced to continue life as
<P>&gt; a warrior. This is what should happen to
<BR>&gt; paladins who lose their way, they would be
<BR>&gt; required to prove their faith by undertaking
<BR>&gt; a great quest before
<P>&gt; they could regain their Paladinhood.
<P>&gt; I really find it hard to beleive more RPers
<BR>&gt; are not appauled by this.
<P>Well, you know what they say is stranger then fiction. It's not that offensive to my RP senses, provided:
<BR>1. The Paladin is attempting to convert the Necromancer
<BR>or
<BR>2. The Necromance stabs the Paladin in the back on their honeymoon.
<P>Now a true blissful union...that I take umbridge at.
<P>SoE
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
